Introduction

Topic: Prostate cancer data analysis Data source: Vanderbilt biostatistics dataset

Main work we did: - Data cleaning - Data wrangling - Building linear regression models and logistic regression models - Nesting and mapping - Data visualisation - Machine learning and Artificial neural network - Principal Component Analysis (PCA)

Data cleaning

  • Importing the file into data table format
  • Conversion of character types into numerical values for better analysis e.g.placebo> 0 mg estrogen
  • Writing variables in more readable format e.g.sz> tumor size

Data analysis

  • Error and Trial method- built lots of linear models using different combinations of varibles
  • At the end, found out the linear model of the highest R squared value stratified on cause of death.

ANOVA test

  • Analysis of Variance (ANOVA) test is a statistical tool to measure how significant the effect of independent variables are within and between groups.

Plots on linear regression models

  • R. squared value is the statistical measure of how close the data fits into the linear regression mdoel.
  • Out of all the trials, systolic_bp ~ diastolic_bp relationship gave the highest R-squared value ranging between 0.23 and 0.79.
  • The left figure shows the positive relationship between systolic and diastolic rates stratified on different causes of death.
  • The right figure shows the adjusted r-squared values for each cause of death in descending order.

plots on activity

  • The patients with normal physical activity showed lowered case number with bone metastasis.

## plots on different doses of estrogen

Serum hemoglobin

  • Generally, people with bone metastasis showed lower serum hemoglobin
  • People of age group 80-90 showed the lowest serum heoglobin.

Highest PA phosphatase observed in the prostate cancer patients

  • The Highest PA phosphatase observed in the prostate cancer patients with bone metastasis.
  • Generally, the level of PA phosphatase is higher for bone mestasis than non-bone metastasis.
